Online tutorial and document reference
http://web.cs.ucla.edu/classes/spring18/cs111/projects/fd_juggling.html
https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Getopt-Long-Option-Example.html
http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/basedefs/fcntl.h.html



the lab0.c includes
#include <stdbool.h> -- provide bool type to use
#include <stdio.h> -- C standard io
#include <stdlib.h> -- C standard library
#include <unistd.h> -- provide POSIX operating system API
#include <getopt.h> -- provide get commandline option API
#include <signal.h> -- provide register signal handler
#include <fcntl.h> -- define requests and arguements used by other functions
#include <errno.h> -- provide error message
#include <string.h> -- provide string




smoke check runs the following test and output success or failure

normal test
run the program without commandline arguement, check exit value of the program

success input test
run the program with --input=input.txt arguement, check exit value of the program

success output test
run the program with --output=output.txt arguement, check exit value of the program

wrong input test
run the program with --input=w_input.txt arguement (w_input.txt have no read permission), check exit value of the program

wrong output test
run the program with --output=w_output.txt arguement (w_output.txt have no write permission), check exit value of the program

catch test
run the program with --segfault --catch arguement, check exit value of the program
